[[File:Isaac Sailmaker Englische Kriegsschiffe.jpg|thumb|300px|''English man-of-war'']]
'''Isaac Sailmaker''' (born '''Isaac Zeilmaker'''  in [[Scheveningen]], 1633; died in [[London]] on June 28, 1721) was a Dutch marine painter active in Britain. He came to London to work for [[George Geldorp]] and later worked for [[Oliver Cromwell]]. He is known for paintings of ships and lighthouses. His painting of [[Eddystone Lighthouse]] is notable as the structure no longer exists.<ref>[http://www.nmm.ac.uk/mag/pages/mnuInDepth/Biography.cfm?biog=217 National Maritime Museum]</ref><ref>[http://collections.rmg.co.uk/collections/objects/13276.html National Maritime Museum]</ref>
